# Collaborative Task Management System Environment Variables

This file serves as an example for the `.env` file. Copy this file to `.env` and fill in the appropriate values for your environment.

---

## Application Configuration

```ini
# Application Environment (e.g., development, production, testing)
APP_ENV=development

# Enable/Disable Debug Mode (true for development, false for production)
APP_DEBUG=true

# Base URL for the PHP backend application (e.g., http://localhost:8000)
APP_URL=http://localhost:8000

# A unique application key for encryption and other security purposes.
# Generate a strong, random string (e.g., using `php -r "echo bin2hex(random_bytes(32));"`).
APP_KEY=your_app_key_here
```

---

## Database Configuration

```ini
# Database connection type (e.g., mysql, pgsql, sqlite)
DB_CONNECTION=mysql

# Database host (e.g., 127.0.0.1, localhost)
DB_HOST=127.0.0.1

# Database port (e.g., 3306 for MySQL, 5432 for PostgreSQL)
DB_PORT=3306

# Database name for the Collaborative Task Management System
DB_DATABASE=task_management_db

# Database username
DB_USERNAME=root

# Database password
DB_PASSWORD=
```

---

## Authentication & Security

```ini
# Secret key for JSON Web Token (JWT) generation and verification.
# This should be a strong, random string.
JWT_SECRET=your_jwt_secret_key_here

# URL for an external authentication service (if used).
# This service might handle user registration, login, and token issuance.
AUTH_SERVICE_URL=http://localhost:3001/api/auth

# API Key to authenticate requests from this service to the external authentication service.
AUTH_SERVICE_API_KEY=your_auth_service_api_key_here
```

---

## Real-time & Cross-Service Communication

```ini
# WebSocket server URL for real-time updates (e.g., task status changes).
# This could be a dedicated WebSocket service or integrated with the backend.
WEBSOCKET_URL=ws://localhost:8080

# Base URL for the Real-time Collaborative Whiteboard service.
# Used for linking or embedding whiteboard functionalities.
WHITEBOARD_SERVICE_URL=http://localhost:3002

# Base URL for the Micro Social Media Dashboard service.
# Used for integrating social features or notifications.
SOCIAL_MEDIA_SERVICE_URL=http://localhost:3003

# Base URL for the Multi-vendor E-commerce Marketplace service.
# Included for cross-project context, though less directly integrated with tasks.
ECOMMERCE_SERVICE_URL=http://localhost:3004
```

---

## Client-Side (React) Configuration

These variables are prefixed with `REACT_APP_` and will be exposed to the client-side React application.

```ini
# Base URL for the Collaborative Task Management System API (PHP backend).
# This is what the React frontend will call.
REACT_APP_API_BASE_URL=http://localhost:8000/api

# Client-side URL for the external authentication service.
REACT_APP_AUTH_SERVICE_URL=http://localhost:3001/api/auth

# Client-side URL for the WebSocket server.
REACT_APP_WEBSOCKET_URL=ws://localhost:8080

# Client-side URL for the Real-time Collaborative Whiteboard service.
REACT_APP_WHITEBOARD_SERVICE_URL=http://localhost:3002

# Client-side URL for the Micro Social Media Dashboard service.
REACT_APP_SOCIAL_MEDIA_SERVICE_URL=http://localhost:3003

# Client-side URL for the Multi-vendor E-commerce Marketplace service.
REACT_APP_ECOMMERCE_SERVICE_URL=http://localhost:3004
```